(Limitations and why the sizing can be too large:) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Peak-based sizing: the network is sized to the hourly peak demand. Short peaks) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  drive large diameters even when the energy-weighted demand is lower. The) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  8-hour smoothed peak is about 8 752 kW) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  versus 9 259 kW instantaneous.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- No temporal diversity inside the optimization: foisonnement is applied once) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  to building peaks, but the optimization still assumes the full diversified) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  peak occurs simultaneously on every branch.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- No thermal losses or return temperature constraints: heat losses, pump) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  constraints, and operational limits are not modelled, so margins are implicitly) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  absorbed by pipe sizing rather than control strategies.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Static resource dispatch: resources are constrained only by max power,) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  with no cost hierarchy, startup limits, or seasonal availability.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(Suggested next steps:) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Re-size pipes based on a design percentile \(e.g., 95th\) or use the 8-hour) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  smoothed peak as the reference.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Add pipe heat losses, pumping power, and velocity constraints to avoid) Tj
0 -14 Td
(  overly large diameters.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Validate demand with measured profiles and update foisonnement per) Tj
